.TH COGCTL 1
.SH NAME
cogctl \- cognitive system control utility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cogctl
[
.B -a
.I atomspace
]
.I command
[
.I args ...
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Cogctl
provides command-line access to Plan9Cog cognitive computing operations.
It allows creating and managing atoms, running PLN inference, and controlling
ECAN attention allocation.
.PP
The
.B -a
option specifies an AtomSpace file to load (not yet implemented).
.PP
The following commands are available:
.TP
.B atom create
.I type name
Create a new atom of the specified type with the given name.
.TP
.B atom list
List all atoms in the AtomSpace.
.TP
.B atom info
.I id
Show detailed information about the atom with the specified ID.
.TP
.B pln stats
Display PLN inference statistics.
.TP
.B ecan update
Update the ECAN attention allocation network.
.TP
.B ecan focus
Show the current attentional focus (top atoms by STI).
.TP
.B info
Display Plan9Cog system information including version, uptime,
atom count, and memory usage.
.SH EXAMPLES
Create a concept node:
.IP
.EX
cogctl atom create 1 'concept:dog'
.EE
.PP
List all atoms:
.IP
.EX
cogctl atom list
.EE
.PP
Show system information:
.IP
.EX
cogctl info
.EE
.PP
Update attention and show focus:
.IP
.EX
cogctl ecan update
cogctl ecan focus
.EE
.SH FILES
.TF /sys/include/plan9cog.h
.TP
.B /sys/include/plan9cog.h
Plan9Cog main header
.SH SOURCE
.B /sys/src/cmd/cogctl
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR cogfs (4),
.IR cogdemo (1),
.IR plan9cog (2)
.SH BUGS
AtomSpace file loading not yet implemented.
